== Etymology == Phlegmasia alba dolens literally means "painful white [[edema]]".<ref>{{cite book | last = Dieulafoy | first = Paul Georges | authorlink = Paul Georges Dieulafoy | coauthors = | title = A Text-book of Medicine | publisher = D. Appleton & Co. | year = 1912 | location = | pages = 488 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=r_MRAAAAYAAJ | doi = | id = | isbn = }}</ref> It received the name "milk leg" because it was once thought to be caused by the [[metastasis]] of milk.<ref>{{cite book | last = Wright | first = Adam Henry | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = A Text-book of Obstetrics | publisher = D. Appleton & Co. | year = 1905 | location = | pages = 473 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=T0ZEJ1dljhUC | doi = | id = | isbn = }}</ref>
